05/11/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- UN war crimes tribunal chief prosecutor Serge Brammertz and Serbian war crimes prosecutor Vladimir Vukcevic discussed technical issues Wednesday (November 4th) related to war crimes proceedings under way in Belgrade and in The Hague.
They also talked about the remaining war crimes fugitives and ways to boost regional co-operation in the field of justice.
Brammertz meets next with President Boris Tadic and Rasim Ljajic, head of Serbia's council for co-operation with The Hague.
In other news, the trial of a Serb suspected of involvement in setting fire to the US Embassy in Belgrade last year opened on Wednesday.
Milan Zivanovic admits he took part in the riots against Kosovo's independence and that he broke into the embassy but denies any involvement in the February 21st 2008 blaze.
Zivanovic is a student at the Faculty of Economics at the University of Belgrade.
(B92, Tanjug, Beta, RTS - 04/11/09)
